<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="111" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="4.[107,1313,1238,2416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[109,462,2065,2098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Hewitt’s Red Rock Hare is widely distributed and presumably has a large population. Overall population is estimated at more than 10,000 adults and predicted to decline at a rate of less than 10% during the next 20 years. Habitat loss has occurred over the past 100 years and is predicted to continue by less than 20% over the next 20 years due to commercial plantations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
